Q
x+2y+2z=2
x=z^2+y^2
Q
(x,y,z)
x=z^2+y^2
x
x = 2-2y-2z
z^2+y^2=2-2y-2z
(z+1)^2+(y+1)^2=4
z^2+y^2 \leq x \leq 2-2y-2z
y,z
0 \leq (z+1)^2+(y+1)^2 \leq 4
y,z
 (z+1)^2 \leq 4-(y+1)^2
-\sqrt{4-(y+1)^2} -1 \leq z \leq \sqrt{4-(y+1)^2} -1
-3 \leq y \leq 1
y+1=r\cos \theta
z+1 = r\sin \theta
y,z
0 \leq r \leq 2
0 \leq \theta \leq 2\pi
x
